Second Department,

June, 1956*

(June 25, 1956) Miriam Zend, Respondent, v. Burrill Zend, Appellant.

Not published with other decisions of June 25, 1956, ante, p. 706.— [Rep.

Motion for a stay granted on condition that appellant perfect the appeal for the September Term, beginning Wednesday, September 12 (for which term the case is set down) and be ready for argument when reached; otherwise, motion denied, with $10 costs. Present—-Wenzel, Acting P. J., Beldoek, Murphy, Ughetta and Kleinfeld, JJ. [See ante, p. 813.]
